Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells cathode often suffers from degradation caused by water vapor in air.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, we report a cathode material, La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta (LSCFN), and evaluate its humidity tolerance by the characterization of the materials in wet air with different water vapor concentration at different temperature.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction analysis indicates that the crystal structure of LSCFN is relatively stable in wet air with no observable impurity.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, a crystalline contraction is observed.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Exposure of wet air to LSCFN causes the decrease of electrical conductivity and increase of polarization resistance because H2O might occupy the active sites for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For long-term operation, higher H2O concentration in air accelerates the degradation of LSCFN cathode.
Titulo: Effect of humidity on La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ cathode of solid oxide fuel cells
